    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I'm at one of those shops that is running Python on Solaris. We build our Python interpreters as 64-bit applications. When building Cython on our Solaris servers, it does not pick up the native C compiler flags from the Python sysconfig. The build defaults to the 32-bit memory model and fails.\r\n\r\nCould Cython's setup.py be enhanced to get these compiler flags from distutils.sysconfig?",
    "closed_at": "2018-10-23T18:22:06Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Cython only manages the .pyx -> .c conversion, from then on it's distutils (or setuptools) that actually invokes the C compiler, which is where this needs to be fixed. ",
